      "lesson title": "Generative Design Tools: Innovation vs Safety",
      "order": 1,
      "Description": "Generative design tools are transforming the way engineers and designers approach problem-solving, offering innovative solutions at remarkable speed. However, relying on AI-generated blueprints without thorough validation can introduce serious safety risks that may not be immediately obvious. This lesson explores the balance between embracing the creative potential of these tools and maintaining the rigorous checks that keep people, products, and projects safe. You will learn to identify where AI-generated outputs may fall short of real-world requirements and understand why human oversight remains an essential part of the design process. By the end of this lesson, you will have a clearer, more confident approach to using generative design tools responsibly and effectively.",
      "status": "draft",
